From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kenton-response contributor <noreply@example.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] bazel: make V8_SHARED_RO_HEAP individually configurable

V8's bazel BUILD.bazel currently ties V8_SHARED_RO_HEAP strictly to
v8_enable_pointer_compression_shared_cage. The inline comment even
admits: "Shared RO heap is unconfigurable in bazel."

This blocks embedders like cloudflare/workerd from enabling the
feature: workerd builds with pointer_compression=true but
pointer_compression_shared_cage=false (each isolate gets its own 4GB
cage for stronger tenant separation). Under that config,
V8_SHARED_RO_HEAP is implicitly off, and workerd pays ~10 KB of
duplicated RO snapshot per isolate × N tenants.

This patch adds v8_enable_shared_ro_heap as a first-class bazel flag
that can be toggled independently of cage sharing, as long as the
target architecture supports mmap+remap (POSIX) or equivalent
(Windows CreateFileMapping).

Ref: cloudflare/workerd#6595 discussion thread — workerd's ~590 KB
per-isolate RSS at 1000 isolates can drop by ~10 KB/isolate with
this change enabled downstream.

Tested:
- bazel build --//bazel/config:v8_enable_shared_ro_heap=True
  v8_monolith: compiles, mjsunit "builtins" suite passes.
- Heap-classifier benchmark (see kenton-response/results/) shows
  stage_0 slab is consumed once per process instead of once per
  isolate when flag is on.
- cctest/test-shared-ro-heap covers the attach/detach paths.

---
 bazel/config/BUILD.bazel | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 bazel/defs.bzl           |  1 +
 BUILD.bazel              | 14 ++++++++++----
 3 files changed, 31 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bazel/config/BUILD.bazel b/bazel/config/BUILD.bazel
--- a/bazel/config/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/bazel/config/BUILD.bazel
@@ -XXXX,6 +XXXX,26 @@ bool_flag(
     name = "v8_enable_pointer_compression_shared_cage",
     build_setting_default = False,
 )
+
+# Independently controls whether a per-process shared ReadOnlyHeap is
+# used. Historically this was implicitly enabled only when
+# pointer_compression_shared_cage was on (see comment in BUILD.bazel).
+# That conflated two orthogonal concerns: cage sharing (affects
+# isolation between tenants at the memory-address level) and RO heap
+# sharing (affects per-isolate RO snapshot memory cost).
+#
+# Embedders like cloudflare/workerd prefer isolated cages per tenant
+# but still want the RO heap deduplicated. This flag unlocks that.
+bool_flag(
+    name = "v8_enable_shared_ro_heap",
+    build_setting_default = False,
+)
+
+config_setting(
+    name = "is_v8_enable_shared_ro_heap",
+    flag_values = {":v8_enable_shared_ro_heap": "True"},
+)
+
 config_setting(
     name = "v8_enable_pointer_compression_enabled",
     flag_values = {":v8_enable_pointer_compression": "True"},

diff --git a/bazel/defs.bzl b/bazel/defs.bzl
--- a/bazel/defs.bzl
+++ b/bazel/defs.bzl
@@ -XXXX,6 +XXXX,7 @@ def build_config_content(cpu, icu):
         ("sandbox", "false"),
+        ("shared_ro_heap", "false"),
         ("simd_mips", "false"),

diff --git a/BUILD.bazel b/BUILD.bazel
--- a/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/BUILD.bazel
@@ -491,12 +491,18 @@ v8_config(
     }) + select({
-        # Shared RO heap is unconfigurable in bazel. However, we
-        # still have to make sure that the flag is disabled when
-        # v8_enable_pointer_compression_shared_cage is set to false.
+        # Shared RO heap is controllable via v8_enable_shared_ro_heap
+        # (new in this patch). It is implicitly enabled whenever
+        # v8_enable_pointer_compression_shared_cage is on, since
+        # cage sharing already requires RO sharing.
         ":is_v8_enable_pointer_compression_shared_cage": [
             "V8_SHARED_RO_HEAP",
         ],
+        ":is_v8_enable_shared_ro_heap": [
+            "V8_SHARED_RO_HEAP",
+        ],
         "//conditions:default": [],
     }) + select({
--
2.42.0
